Witness Reporter THE KwaZulu-Natal Health Department has suspended the acting CEO of the Church of Scotland Hospital in Msinga, T.N. Dube, pending disciplinary action after numerous complaints from staff and the public. Department of Health spokesperson Chris Maxon said in a statement yesterday that the department has received numerous complaints alleging acts of corruption and nepotism and said a disciplinary hearing will be instituted soon. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  